snippet.textDisplay: I totally agree that we should respect wildlife. However, here is the expert on wildlife policy explaining the mechanism of the virus transmission. A professor should not comment on things he cannot be sure enough. Besides that, suppose the reasoning is right, should there be a professor telling us why there isn’t any COV19 in 2018 in China? Lastly, virus is mysterious and people like to draw conclusions which makes them feel good. If drawing a conclusion is easy, the world would be out of order. Even scientists are still baffled right now and the editor of the documentary is suspicious of getting more audience via revoking people’s empathy with such a overconfident conclusion.
